- Run MAMP
- Install Wordpress.org download file and change the file name to your website name
- Go to MAMP Preferences and point your website folder to the Wordpress folder with your website Name
- Click Start WebPage
- Go to phpMyAdmin and create a database
- Find and Note Your 
 Database name 
 Database username 
 Database password 
 Database host 
- Delete the /MAMP/ from the url to open up the wordpress intro screen
- Continue and enter in the details asked
- Continue with the installation Process and make a UserName and Password
- Your website should be up and running.
